cs.NE, cs.DM, cs.DS, cs.GT, cs.IT. 

The paper deals with the optimization problem of designing large and low-cost communication networks, which involves graph theory, optimization, and algorithm design. Therefore, cs.NE (Networks and Communications), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.IT (Information Theory) are all relevant sub-categories. Among these, cs.NE and cs.DM are the most likely categories as they directly relate to the problem of designing communication networks and the optimization techniques used in the paper. cs.DS and cs.GT are also relevant as they deal with algorithm design and optimization, while cs.IT is less likely as it focuses more on information theory and coding.
